<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-10T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="1320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1320">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/105.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Miller</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-10T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your June 5, 10 p.m. Please report full result of meeting of Oil
                            Association, held Saturday night, and what action was taken regarding
                            loan of two hundred thousand pesos requested by Constitutionalists.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>